                - var object = {}
                - object['A'] ='<p><b>An Attorney</b> – An attorney is a person admitted to practice law in at least one jurisdiction to perform criminal and civil legal functions on behalf of clients.</p><p><b>Accounting or Accountancy</b> – Accounting basically is a service-based profession that provides reliable and relevant financial information, which is useful in making sound business decisions.</p><p><b>Accrual Basis</b> – It is a method of accounting in which each item is entered as it is earned or incurred regardless of when actual payments are received or made.</p><p><b>Assets</b> – Assets acquired in operating activities are called revenues.</p><p><b>Advertising</b> – Advertising is a form of communication for marketing and used to encourage, persuade, or manipulate an audience (viewers, readers or listeners; sometimes a specific group) to continue or take some new action.</p>'
                - object['B'] =''
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Business Plans</b> – A business plan is an essential roadmap for business’ success. This living document outlines the route a company intends to take to grow revenues.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Business Goals</b> – It is a mission statement company sets to achieve the goals during its time in operation.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Blogs</b> – Blogs are usually used by individuals to record their observations and experiences.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Brokers</b> – Brokers are third party distributors who often buy directly from the distributor or wholesaler and sell it to retailers or end users.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Business Licenses</b> – Business Licenses are permits issued by government agencies that allow individuals to conduct business.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Board of Equalization</b> – California collects California state sales and use tax, as well as fuel, alcohol, and tobacco taxes and fees that provide revenue for state government and essential funding for counties, cities, and special districts.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Business Property Insurance</b> – It is a must to protect your company’s assets. It also protects commercial property from perils such as fire, burning, and theft. Business property insurance is a must to protect your company\'s assets.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Bank Reconciliation</b> – It is a process that explains the difference between the bank balance shown in company’s bank statement, as supplied by the bank, and the corresponding amount shown in the organization\'s own accounting records at a particular point in time.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Balance Sheet</b> – A balance statement of financial position is a summary of the financial balances of a company.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Bank Statement</b> – Bank statement is a list of all transactions which occurred during a particular period of time and impacted cash in bank account of business. Such a statement is prepared by the bank and is provided to the company owning the bank account.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Break-even Analysis</b> – It is a technique widely used by production management accountants. It is used to determine when your business will be able to cover all of its expenses and begin to make a profit.</p>'
                - object['B'] += '<p><b>Business Description</b> – Business description allows you to get your ideas, plans and visions down on paper before you go any further. It is important to have a thorough understanding of what your business is, and the direction that you intend it to follow.</p>'
                - object['C'] = ''
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Corporation</b> – It is a separate legal entity that has been incorporated through a legislative process established through legislation.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Consultant</b> – A consultant is a person who provides professional advice in specific area of specialization such as Computer Technology, Engineering, Technology, Mechanics, etc.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Competitor Analysis</b> – Competitor analysis in marketing and strategic management is an assessment of the strengths and weaknesses of current and potential competitors.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Chamber of Commerce</b> – It is a form of business network. It is also referred to as a board of trade.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Common Area Maintenance (CAM)</b> – A common area maintenance charge refers to the fees paid by tenants. Such fees are usually paid to the landlord to recompense operating, repairing and maintaining charges.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Creditor</b> - A creditor is a person, bank, and other enterprise that has lent money to another party.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Cash Basis Method</b> – The cash method of accounting records revenue when cash is received, and records expenses when cash is paid.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Cash Flow Statement</b> – Cash flow statement predicts company’s cash balances in the future.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Contributed Capital</b> – Contributed capital is a component of equity resulting from the contributions of the capital resources from the owners.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Cash Ledger</b> – It is an accounting book of prime entry listing all the transactions that impacted cash in bank and this book is prepared by the accountant.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Credit History</b> – A credit history shows an individual\'s past record of paying bills, loans, etc. It is also used to verify that they are financially responsible.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Collateral</b> – Collateral are those personal and business assets that can be sold to pay back the loan. Every loan program, even many microloan programs, requires at least some collateral to secure a loan.</p>'
                - object['C'] += '<p><b>Cash Flow </b> – Cash flow is the movement of money into or out of a business, project, or financial product. It is usually measured during a specified, limited period of time.</p>'
                - object['D'] = ''
                - object['D'] += '<p><b>DBA (Doing Business As)</b> – It is a legal term used in United States of America. It is a fictions term used under which one can conduct business. It is not an actual name of the business one conducts or is responsible for.</p>'
                - object['D'] += '<p><b>Distribution</b>– Distribution is the way in which the equity is distributed amongst the various stock-holders.</p>'
                - object['E'] = ''
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>Entrepreneur</b> – Entrepreneur is a person who organizes and manages any enterprise, especially a business, usually with considerable initiative and risk.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>External Communication</b> – It includes email, brochures, newsletters, posters, advertisements and other forms of multimedia marketing designed to attract customers, partners and suppliers to conduct profitable business transactions.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>Excess Liability Coverage</b> – Excess liability is insurance coverage that typically provides coverage beyond that of an underlying policy such as an automobile or homeowner’s policy.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>Equity</b> – Equity is what the company “owes” to the owners. If a company goes bankrupt, liabilities are paid off first to the creditors, while equity is the last to be distributed.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>Expenses</b> – Assets used in the process of generating revenues are called expenses.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>Earnings before Income Tax</b> – It is an indicator of a company’s profitability, calculated as net income minus interest and tax.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>E-Mail Marketing</b> – Email marketing is directly marketing a commercial message to a group of people using email. Every email sent to a potential or current customer could be considered email marketing.</p>'
                - object['E'] += '<p><b>Executive Summary</b> – It is a regular exercise in corporate world of giving executives a concise outline of the main points in a report, indicting where in the report look for detailed information.</p>'
                - object['F'] = ''
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Federal Licenses and Permits</b> – If your business is regulated by federal government, you may need to obtain a federal license.</p>'
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Financial Accounting</b> – A field of accounting that treats money as a means of measuring economic performance instead of as a factor of production.</p>'
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Financial Statement</b> – A financial statement is a formal record of the financial activities of a business, person, or other entity.</p>'
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Financial Reporting</b> – Financial reporting is a process through which companies communicate information to the public.</p>'
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Fixed (overhead) expenses</b> – A fixed (overhead) cost refers to a specific type or group of business expenses. The word overhead in business is used to describe the cost of doing business or the amount of money an individual or company must spend in order to run and maintain a functional business.</p>'
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Forecasts</b> – It is also referred to as forecasting. It is the process of making statements about events whose actual outcomes (typically) have not yet been observed.</p>'
                - object['F'] += '<p><b>Franchising</b> – Franchising is the practice of using another firm\'s successful business model.</p>'
                - object['G'] = ''
                - object['G'] += '<p><b>General Partnership</b> – Each of the two or partners will have unlimited liability for the debts of the business.</p>'
                - object['G'] += '<p><b>Gross Margin</b> – Gross margin ratio is the ratio of a business to its revenue. It is a profitability measuring what proportion of revenue is converted into gross profits.</p>'
                - object['I'] = ''
                - object['I'] += '<p><b>Internal Communication</b> – It is the function responsible for effective communication or trade among participants within an organization, including states.</p>'
                - object['I'] += '<p><b>Investor</b> – An investor is an individual who commits money to investment products with the expectation of financial return.</p>'
                - object['I'] += '<p><b>Income Statement</b> – It is company’s financial performance measured for over a certain period of time.</p>'
                - object['I'] += '<p><b>Income Tax</b> – Tax directly levied on an individual’s company or company’s income is called Income Tax.</p>'
                - object['J'] = ''
                - object['K'] = ''
                - object['L'] = ''
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Limited Partnership</b> – Two or more partners unite to conduct a business.</p>'
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Limited Liability</b> – It is a concept through which person\'s liability is limited to a fixed value of a person\'s investment in a company.</p>'
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Liability</b> – A liability is defined as an obligation of an entity arising from past transactions or events, the settlement of which may result in the transfer or use of assets, provision of services or other yielding of economic benefits in the future.</p>'
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Local Licenses and Permits</b> –It is an agreement between government and an entrepreneur which requires an entrepreneur to comply with the local, state and federal laws in order to conduct businesses in a specific territory.</p>'
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Liability Insurance</b> – Insurance that protects a company and the owner of the company in the event of a formal lawsuit or other third party claim.</p>'
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Life Insurance</b> –The term, ‘Life Insurance’ is an assurance of an individual’s life in the event of untimely death.  It provides coverage at fixed rate of payments for a limited period of time.</p>'
                - object['L'] += '<p><b>Loan Proposal</b> – Loan proposal is usually prepared and presented by bank’s officer.</p>'
                - object['M'] = ''
