                - object['P'] += '<p><b>Pre-employment Screening Service</b> – This service helps to check and verify the background of an employee to be recruited.</p>'
                - object['P'] += '<p><b>Permits</b> – It allows/permits someone to do something within the legal norms.</p>'
                - object['Q'] = ''
                - object['R'] = ''
                - object['R'] += '<p><b>Retained Earnings</b> – It refers to the sum of net income which is retained by the company rather than distributed to its owners as share.</p>'
                - object['R'] += '<p><b>Revenue</b> – It is income that a company receives from its business operations such as business activities, usually from the sale of goods and services to customers.</p>'
                - object['R'] += '<p><b>Reality Checks</b> - An assessment to determine if one\'s circumstances or expectations conform to reality.</p>'
                - object['S'] = ''
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>Software</b> – Software is any set of machine-readable instructions that directs a computer\'s processor to perform specific operations.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>Strategic Technology Plan</b> – It is a specific type of strategy plan that lets an organization know where they are and where they want to be sometime in future in regards of technology and infrastructure.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>Sole Proprietorship</b> – It is a type of business entity that is owned and run by an individual.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>"S" Corporation</b> – It is corporation that makes a valid election to be taxed under subchapter S chapter 1 of the Internal Revenue Code.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>State Licenses and Permits</b> – The state in which you propose to conduct business may require you to have special licenses and permits to do business.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>The Seller’s Permit</b> – A seller’s permit allows you to collect sale taxes from customers and your clients, which you in turn pay to the state, local or federal government.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>Start up Cost</b> – The required amount of money to set up a new business.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>SBS Loan</b> – Loans provided to small businesses for various purposes by a lender. These loans may have less restrictive requirements, enabling the small business to secure the funds.</p>'
                - object['S'] += '<p><b>Strategic Planning</b> – Strategic planning is an organization\'s process of defining its strategy, or direction, and making decisions on allocating its resources to pursue this strategy.</p>'
                - object['T'] = ''
                - object['T'] += '<p><b>Trademark</b> – It is a brand name or sign, or symbol which represents a particular name, source or company.</p>'
                - object['T'] += '<p><b>Tradeshow Marketing</b> –Tradeshow Marketing is large exposition to promote awareness and sales of especially new products within an industry.</p>'
                - object['U'] = ''
                - object['V'] = ''
                - object['V'] += '<p><b>Veto</b> - It is the power of an officer of the state to officially stop the unilaterally a piece of legislation.</p>'
                - object['V'] += '<p><b>Variable (related to business sales) Expenses</b> - Variable costs are directly related to business sale. They change with the volume of the product you sel</p>'
                - object['W'] = ''
                - object['W'] += '<p><b>Workers Compensation Insurance</b> - It helps protect your employees from injuries in the course of employment and keeps you in compliance with workers compensation laws.</p>'
                - object['X'] = ''
                - object['Y'] = ''
                - object['Z'] = ''
